        "title": "Java: Filtering out user input using nextInt()",
        "body": "<p>I am making a program where the user enters their mark, if they enter over 100 then the program stops, however I can't seem to stop the value over 100 also being assigned to the Marks variable...<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);\nInt Marks = 0;\n\nwhile (Marks &gt;= 0 &amp;&amp; Marks &lt;= 100) {\n        System.out.println(\"Enter Students Test Marks Here\");\n\n        Marks = input.nextInt();\n}\n\n// Output Test\nSystem.out.println(\"The Marks variable value is \" +Marks);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
